{
  "texts": [
    "We manually checked that the AI stimuli were neutral in terms of linguistic variation, avoiding any explicitly American or British dialect usage (e.g., spelling variations such as \"s\" vs. \"z\" in, for example, the word \"humanize\").",
    "This was done to ensure that participants, whatever their dialect, could understand the sentences without cultural or ethnic bias, and to reduce the risk of their judging sentence quality based on these variations.",
    "The study lasted approximately 20 min and participants were compensated with a $10 gift voucher.",
    "After welcoming the participants, the experimenter provided a description of the study and a consent form to the participants.",
    "The description informed the participants in broad terms that the study aimed to determine how people evaluate sentences in the context of human-robot interaction."
  ]
}